neighborhood_overview:
Very centrally located.

Fishermans Wharf, Chinatown, North Beach, downtown, Union Square shopping, Polk Street action, are all within walking distant.

For those who prefer to ride, public transport, including the classic cable car lines, are conveniently close.

Nob Hill is Old San Francisco, filled with the cable cars and classic Victorian architecture the city is famous for.

It's also a rich neighborhood with luxury buildings and nice restaurants and expansive views of the bay and beyond. There are a Trader Joes and a Whole Foods within walking distance, not to mention a cute gourmet market on the corner one block up.

For the party-minded, Polk Street and its remarkable night life are just three blocks away.

We are very interested in swapping housing also.
